Greek Opposition Leader Says Austerity Failed, Frankfurter Says

-- B y   N a o m i   K r e s g e
-- 
2011-10-20T16:15:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/greek-opposition-leader-says-austerity-failed-frankfurter-says.html
Antonis Samaras, leader of  Greece ’s
biggest opposition party, said the austerity measures imposed on
the country have failed, writing in an opinion column in
 Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung .  “The Greek public is in despair, because despite their
sacrifices they see no improvement,” Samaras, who heads the New
Democracy party, wrote in the German newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Naomi Kresge in Berlin at 
 nkresge@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at 
 pserafino@bloomberg.net  